OASISFormat: 0.3
Name: fut
Version: %%VERSION%%
Synopsis: Future values for asynchronous programming in OCaml
Maintainers: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>
Authors: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>
Copyrights: (c) 2012 Daniel C. Bünzli
License: BSD3
Homepage: http://erratique.ch/software/fut
Description:
 Fut is an OCaml module for asynchronous programming in OCaml. It
 provides support to program with future values. A future value is a
 value becomes available at some point in the future.
 .
 Fut is made of a single module, it depends on OCaml's Unix and Thread modules 
 and is distributed under the BSD3 license.

